value.0: Greetings, <Sir/Madam>.  I bid you welcome to the Temple of the Triad's Light.  I trust you have business within the halls of our faith?
Of course, I would be happy to offer you a selection of worthy aids.  May they serve you well.

The Triad is what the faiths of Ilmater, Torm and Tyr are called together.  The three faiths draw strength on each other to work towards lawfulness, faith, duty and sacrifice.  As a whole, we strive to better all the people of Faerun by offering protection and aid from any that would seek to harm or control them wrongfully.  We work together where working as one would falter.

Tyr is known as the Even-handed.  He seeks justice and resolve within law.  Through his teachings, we bring order where there may be chaos, punishment to the wicked, and prosperity through fair justice.  Many a Tyrran priest has served in courts, aiding in the pursuit of justice, just as others have taken more active roles in ensuring justice does not go unhindered.

We do exactly as we have always done.  We work to insure justice is done.  There are times when our resolve for justice is needed.  During those times, we are called upon to make sure that there is fairness.
Go right ahead.
If you would speak on the teachings of Ilmater, perhaps High Priest Kellinanah Kross would be good company.
Perhaps, if you would like to speak on Torm, you should seek out High Priest Haulfest.
Yes.  We may have three faiths, but those three faiths are stronger as one.  We of the Triad have always worked together to one end.

Each of us here have our own duties that we help Kohlingen with.  William Haulfest tends to most of the needs of those who pass through this city.  Kellinanah Kross tends to the ill and injured.  My tasks are mostly helping Kohlingen maintain its laws and making sure that those are carried justly.
Who did you wish to know about?

Marinsbane is a noble, but humble man.  He has long served Kohlingen, keeping the city protected and in good order.  He can be gruff at times, but he acts for the best of the city.  He is the person you should speak with if you have any need for information regarding the Kohlinger military.  There are few things he does not know.

Kellinanah and I go back a few years.  We have become good friends and I trust her compassion and loyalty to Ilmater and the Triad.   She has always strived to the ideals of the Crying God and there is no other I would trust more to further his ends here with us.

William Haulfest is a good man and a priest dedicated to Torm.  He used to serve Cordor until the Waukeens moved in.  After that, he came here.  It wasn't until this temple was founded when he found a calling he could not deny.  He is proud to be helping again.

We do our duties respectively, as we can.  Even though we may be of three faiths, our tasks all fall together.  We help Kohlingen and those of these lands in the ways we know how, just as many others do.
I should be leaving.  Thank you for your time.  Farewell.
I need equipment to help me fighting evil and injustice.
Thank you.
Triad?  Everyone keeps speaking of the Triad.  What can you tell me of it or them?
Let me ask you about this temple here.  What is its purpose?
What can you tell me on Tyr?
So what duties do you perform here, in Kohlingen?  The city seems to be one of law and justice...
I see.  Let me ask you something else then.
What can you tell me on Ilmater?
What can you tell me on Torm?
I will do that.  Farewell.
What is the purpose of this temple here in Kohlingen?  Three gods dedicated in one temple?
What do you do here, though?
What about the others of Kohlingen?
No one right now.
Justicar Marinsbane.  What do you know about him?
Kellinanah Kross.  What do you know about her?
William Haulfest.  What do you know of William Haulfest.
So you three carry on your duties as you can?
